HEADWORD: Unsensualize
<hw>Un*sen"su*al*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>sensualize</ets>.]</ety> <def>To elevate from the
domain of the senses; to purify.</def> <rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

